.TH JPEGLS 1 "2026-02-15" "JLSwift 0.1.0" "JPEG-LS Compression Tool"
.SH NAME
jpegls \- JPEG-LS command-line tool for encoding and decoding
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B jpegls
[\fB\-\-version\fR]
[\fB\-\-help\fR]
.I command
[\fIoptions\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B jpegls
is a command-line tool for working with JPEG-LS compressed image files. JPEG-LS (ISO/IEC 14495-1:1999 / ITU-T.87) is a lossless/near-lossless compression standard specifically designed for continuous-tone images, widely used in medical imaging (DICOM) due to its excellent compression ratio while maintaining image fidelity.
.PP
JLSwift provides a native Swift implementation optimized for Apple Silicon with hardware acceleration support, while maintaining compatibility with x86-64 systems.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B encode
Encode raw pixel data to JPEG-LS format.
.TP
.B decode
Decode JPEG-LS file to raw pixel data.
.TP
.B info
Display information about a JPEG-LS file.
.TP
.B verify
Verify JPEG-LS file integrity and validate structure.
.TP
.B batch
Process multiple JPEG-LS files in batch with parallel processing.
.TP
.B completion
Generate shell completion scripts for bash, zsh, or fish.
.SH ENCODE COMMAND
.B jpegls encode
[\fIoptions\fR]
.I input-file output-file
.PP
Encode raw pixel data to JPEG-LS format. Requires image dimensions and parameters.
.SS Options
.TP
.BR \-w ", " \-\-width " " \fIpixels\fR
Image width in pixels (required).
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-height " " \fIpixels\fR
Image height in pixels (required).
.TP
.BR \-b ", " \-\-bits\-per\-sample " " \fIbits\fR
Bits per sample, range 2-16 (default: 8).
.TP
.BR \-c ", " \-\-components " " \fIcount\fR
Number of components: 1 for grayscale, 3 for RGB (default: 1).
.TP
.B \-\-near \fIvalue\fR
NEAR parameter for near-lossless encoding. 0 for lossless, 1-255 for lossy (default: 0).
.TP
.B \-\-interleave \fImode\fR
Interleaving mode: \fBnone\fR, \fBline\fR, or \fBsample\fR (default: none).
Single-component images always use 'none'.
.TP
.B \-\-color\-transform \fItransform\fR
Color transformation: \fBnone\fR, \fBhp1\fR, \fBhp2\fR, or \fBhp3\fR (default: none).
.TP
.B \-\-t1 \fIvalue\fR
Custom T1 threshold parameter (optional).
.TP
.B \-\-t2 \fIvalue\fR
Custom T2 threshold parameter (optional).
.TP
.B \-\-t3 \fIvalue\fR
Custom T3 threshold parameter (optional).
.TP
.B \-\-reset \fIvalue\fR
Custom RESET value for context reinitialization (optional).
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Enable verbose output with encoding progress.
.TP
.BR \-q ", " \-\-quiet
Suppress non-essential output (quiet mode).
.SS Examples
.TP
Encode grayscale image (lossless):
.B jpegls encode
input.raw output.jls \fB\-\-width\fR 512 \fB\-\-height\fR 512
.TP
Encode RGB image with line interleaving:
.B jpegls encode
input.raw output.jls \fB\-\-width\fR 512 \fB\-\-height\fR 512 \fB\-\-components\fR 3 \fB\-\-interleave\fR line
.TP
Near-lossless encoding (NEAR=3):
.B jpegls encode
input.raw output.jls \fB\-\-width\fR 512 \fB\-\-height\fR 512 \fB\-\-near\fR 3 \fB\-\-verbose\fR
.PP
\fBNote:\fR Full encode functionality requires bitstream writer integration, currently in development.
.SH DECODE COMMAND
.B jpegls decode
[\fIoptions\fR]
.I input-file output-file
.PP
Decode JPEG-LS file to raw pixel data.
.SS Options
.TP
.B \-\-format \fIformat\fR
Output format: \fBraw\fR, \fBpng\fR, or \fBtiff\fR (default: raw).
PNG and TIFF support is planned.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Enable verbose output with decoding progress.
.TP
.BR \-q ", " \-\-quiet
Suppress non-essential output (quiet mode).
.SS Examples
.TP
Decode to raw format:
.B jpegls decode
input.jls output.raw
.TP
Decode with verbose output:
.B jpegls decode
input.jls output.raw \fB\-\-verbose\fR
.PP
\fBNote:\fR Full decode functionality requires bitstream reader integration, currently in development.
.SH INFO COMMAND
.B jpegls info
[\fIoptions\fR]
.I input-file
.PP
Display detailed information about a JPEG-LS file, including frame header, scan headers, preset parameters, and compression statistics.
.SS Options
.TP
.B \-\-json
Output in JSON format for programmatic use.
.TP
.BR \-q ", " \-\-quiet
Minimal output: single line with essential information only.
Format: "WIDTHxHEIGHT BITS-bit COMPONENTS-component ENCODING"
.SS Examples
.TP
Human-readable output:
.B jpegls info
image.jls
.TP
JSON output:
.B jpegls info
image.jls \fB\-\-json\fR
.TP
Quiet mode (single line):
.B jpegls info
image.jls \fB\-\-quiet\fR
.SH VERIFY COMMAND
.B jpegls verify
[\fIoptions\fR]
.I input-file
.PP
Validate JPEG-LS file structure and parameters. Checks file integrity, marker segments, header validity, and parameter consistency.
.SS Verification Steps
.IP \(bu 2
File structure validity (SOI, SOF, SOS, EOI markers)
.IP \(bu 2
Frame header parameters (dimensions, bits per sample, component count)
.IP \(bu 2
Scan header consistency with frame header
.IP \(bu 2
Preset parameter validity and threshold ordering (T1 ≤ T2 ≤ T3 ≤ MAXVAL)
.IP \(bu 2
Component ID consistency across headers
.SS Options
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Enable verbose output with detailed validation steps.
.TP
.BR \-q ", " \-\-quiet
Suppress all output. Exit code 0 indicates success, non-zero indicates failure.
.SS Examples
.TP
Basic verification:
.B jpegls verify
image.jls
.TP
Verbose verification:
.B jpegls verify
image.jls \fB\-\-verbose\fR
.TP
Quiet mode (no output):
.B jpegls verify
image.jls \fB\-\-quiet\fR
.SH BATCH COMMAND
.B jpegls batch
[\fIoptions\fR]
.I operation input-pattern
.PP
Process multiple JPEG-LS files in parallel with encode, decode, info, or verify operations. Supports glob patterns for file matching and configurable parallelism.
.SS Arguments
.TP
.I operation
Operation to perform: \fBencode\fR, \fBdecode\fR, \fBinfo\fR, or \fBverify\fR.
.TP
.I input-pattern
Glob pattern (e.g., "*.jls", "images/*.raw") or directory path.
.SS Options
.TP
.BR \-o ", " \-\-output\-dir " " \fIdirectory\fR
Output directory for processed files (required for encode/decode).
.TP
.BR \-w ", " \-\-width " " \fIpixels\fR
Image width in pixels (required for encode operation).
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-height " " \fIpixels\fR
Image height in pixels (required for encode operation).
.TP
.BR \-b ", " \-\-bits\-per\-sample " " \fIbits\fR
Bits per sample, range 2-16 (default: 8, for encode operation).
.TP
.BR \-c ", " \-\-components " " \fIcount\fR
Number of components: 1 or 3 (default: 1, for encode operation).
.TP
.B \-\-near \fIvalue\fR
NEAR parameter, 0=lossless, 1-255=lossy (default: 0, for encode operation).
.TP
.B \-\-interleave \fImode\fR
Interleave mode: \fBnone\fR, \fBline\fR, or \fBsample\fR (default: none, for encode operation).
.TP
.B \-\-color\-transform \fItransform\fR
Color transformation: \fBnone\fR, \fBhp1\fR, \fBhp2\fR, or \fBhp3\fR (default: none, for encode operation).
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-parallelism " " \fIcount\fR
Maximum number of parallel operations (default: CPU count).
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Show detailed progress for each file.
.TP
.BR \-q ", " \-\-quiet
Suppress all output except errors.
.TP
.B \-\-fail\-fast
Stop processing on first error (default: continue processing all files).
.SS Examples
.TP
Get info for all .jls files:
.B jpegls batch info
"images/*.jls"
.TP
Verify all JPEG-LS files with verbose output:
.B jpegls batch verify
"/path/to/images/*.jls" \fB\-\-verbose\fR
.TP
Process with custom parallelism:
.B jpegls batch verify
"*.jls" \fB\-\-parallelism\fR 2
.TP
Stop on first error:
.B jpegls batch info
"*.jls" \fB\-\-fail\-fast\fR
.SH COMPLETION COMMAND
.B jpegls completion
.I shell
.PP
Generate shell completion scripts for bash, zsh, or fish shells. Install the generated script according to your shell's conventions to enable tab completion.
.SS Arguments
.TP
.I shell
Shell type: \fBbash\fR, \fBzsh\fR, or \fBfish\fR.
.SS Installation
.PP
.B Bash:
.IP
# System-wide installation
.br
.B sudo jpegls completion bash
> /etc/bash_completion.d/jpegls
.IP
# User installation
.br
.B jpegls completion bash
> ~/.local/share/bash-completion/completions/jpegls
.PP
.B Zsh:
.IP
# System-wide installation
.br
.B sudo jpegls completion zsh
> /usr/local/share/zsh/site-functions/_jpegls
.IP
# User installation
.br
.B mkdir -p ~/.zfunc
.br
.B jpegls completion zsh
> ~/.zfunc/_jpegls
.br
# Add to ~/.zshrc: fpath=(~/.zfunc $fpath)
.PP
.B Fish:
.IP
# User installation
.br
.B mkdir -p ~/.config/fish/completions
.br
.B jpegls completion fish
> ~/.config/fish/completions/jpegls.fish
.PP
After installation, restart your shell or source the completion file to enable tab completion.
.SS Examples
.TP
Generate bash completion:
.B jpegls completion bash
> jpegls-completion.bash
.TP
Generate zsh completion:
.B jpegls completion zsh
> _jpegls
.TP
Generate fish completion:
.B jpegls completion fish
> jpegls.fish
.SH GLOBAL OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-version
Display version information.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Display help information. Use with a command to show command-specific help.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Successful execution.
.TP
.B 1
Error occurred (invalid arguments, file not found, parsing error, etc.).
.SH DICOM COMPATIBILITY
JLSwift supports DICOM transfer syntaxes for medical imaging:
.TP
.B 1.2.840.10008.1.2.4.80
JPEG-LS Lossless Image Compression
.TP
.B 1.2.840.10008.1.2.4.81
JPEG-LS Lossy (Near-Lossless) Image Compression
.SH PERFORMANCE
JLSwift is optimized for Apple Silicon (M1/M2/M3) with ARM NEON/SIMD acceleration and Apple Accelerate framework integration. It also supports x86-64 systems with SSE/AVX optimizations.
.PP
The implementation includes memory optimization features:
.IP \(bu 2
Buffer pooling for reduced allocation overhead
.IP \(bu 2
Tile-based processing for large images
.IP \(bu 2
Cache-friendly data layouts for improved performance
.SH FILES
.TP
.B /etc/bash_completion.d/jpegls
System-wide bash completion script.
.TP
.B ~/.local/share/bash-completion/completions/jpegls
User-specific bash completion script.
.TP
.B /usr/local/share/zsh/site-functions/_jpegls
System-wide zsh completion script.
.TP
.B ~/.zfunc/_jpegls
User-specific zsh completion script.
.TP
.B ~/.config/fish/completions/jpegls.fish
Fish shell completion script.
.SH STANDARDS
.B jpegls
implements the JPEG-LS standard as defined in:
.IP \(bu 2
ISO/IEC 14495-1:1999 - Lossless and near-lossless compression of continuous-tone still images
.IP \(bu 2
ITU-T Recommendation T.87 (identical to ISO/IEC 14495-1)
.SH BUGS
.IP \(bu 2
Full encode functionality requires bitstream writer integration (in development).
.IP \(bu 2
Full decode functionality requires bitstream reader integration (in development).
.IP \(bu 2
PNG and TIFF output formats for decode command are planned but not yet implemented.
.IP \(bu 2
Custom preset parameters (--t1, --t2, --t3, --reset) are not yet supported by the encoder.
.PP
Report bugs at: https://github.com/Raster-Lab/JLSwift/issues
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Display information about a JPEG-LS file:
.IP
.B jpegls info
medical-image.jls
.PP
Verify file integrity:
.IP
.B jpegls verify
medical-image.jls \fB\-\-verbose\fR
.PP
Encode a grayscale medical image:
.IP
.B jpegls encode
ct-scan.raw ct-scan.jls \e
.br
  \fB\-\-width\fR 512 \fB\-\-height\fR 512 \fB\-\-bits\-per\-sample\fR 12
.PP
Encode RGB image with sample interleaving:
.IP
.B jpegls encode
photo.raw photo.jls \e
.br
  \fB\-\-width\fR 1920 \fB\-\-height\fR 1080 \e
.br
  \fB\-\-components\fR 3 \fB\-\-interleave\fR sample
.PP
Near-lossless encoding with NEAR=2:
.IP
.B jpegls encode
image.raw image.jls \e
.br
  \fB\-\-width\fR 1024 \fB\-\-height\fR 768 \fB\-\-near\fR 2
.PP
Batch verify all JPEG-LS files in a directory:
.IP
.B jpegls batch verify
"dicom-images/*.jls" \fB\-\-parallelism\fR 4
.PP
Batch get info with quiet mode:
.IP
.B jpegls batch info
"*.jls" \fB\-\-quiet\fR
